A 16-year-old boy, (name withheld) has been arrested by men of the Ogun State Police Command for stealing woman’s 14 pants. The suspect, according to a statement by the command’s Public Relations Officer, DSP Abimbola Oyeyemi, was arrested following a report by Amudalat Opaleye, a resident of Kano Street, Ayetoro. The statement added that the victim reported at Ayetoro police station that at about 6 am of Tuesday 18th of August 2020, the suspect sneaked into her room and stole her pants, but while trying to sneak out, he was caught with the pants. Oyeyemi said, “upon the report, the DPO Ayetoro, CSP Mobolaji Jimoh detailed his detectives to the scene, where the suspect was promptly arrested”. He added that “a search warrant was executed in his dwelling house and another 14 used woman pants were recovered there. “He has confessed to the crime but claimed that he was sent by somebody to get those pants for him.” Oyeyemi added that effort was on top gear to get his so-called accomplice arrested. Meanwhile, the State Commissioner of Police, Edward Awolowo Ajogun, has directed that the suspect be transferred to the state criminal investigation and intelligence department for further investigation. Vanguard By James Ogunnaike - Abeokuta Operatives of the Ogun State Command of the Nigeria Police have arrested a 22-year-old vulcanizer, Dele Ope, for allegedly stealing a pant of her client for money ritual. The Police Public Relations Officer, Ogun State command, DSP Abimbola Oyeyemi, who revealed this in a statement… June 21, 2020 In "Metro" ABEOKUTA—Men of Ogun State Police Command have arrested a 65-year-old man, Alosuposo Louis, a radio repairer, for allegedly raping two minors, aged 10 and eight years. January 27, 2017 In "News" During interrogation, Ifeanyi said he broke into the house at about 2am and headed straight to the line where some pants were hanged.  He was putting them into his bag when he was apprehended January 20, 2019 In "Crime Alert"